				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\mathrm{TER}=\frac{\mathrm{The \,rate \,of\,temperature\, increase\, in\, the \,presence \,of \,nanoparticles}}{\mathrm{The\, rate\, of \,temperature\, increase\, in\, the \,absence \,of \,nanoparticles}}.$$\end{document}

Furthermore, Kallumadil et al. (2009) introduced the system-independent intrinsic loss power (ILP), as a standard alternative for SAR, which is given in Eq. 4:4ILP=SARH2×f,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
